div.h1: Linker Script: Physical vs Virtual Address Spaces

g.text: BSS: Disk vs RAM vs Zeroed
In RAM after load: GARBAGE (BIOS POST patterns)
After rep stosd: all zeros kmain safe
1. Build page tables while paging OFF
2. Load CR3 with PHYSICAL PD address
mov cr3, pd_phys; TLB flushed on CR3 write
3. Set CR0.PG=1 POINT OF NO RETURN
or cr0, 0x80000000; next fetch goes through page tables
jmp via fn-ptr to higher-half; remove PDE[0]=0; reload CR3
SHT_NOBITS: 0 bytes in ELF on disk
must run before any C global access
bootloader copies ELF segments; BSS has no bytes to copy
Higher-half map (permanent): virt 0xC0100000 -> phys 0x00100000; PDE[768] U/S=0 G=1
Identity map (boot only): virt=phys=0x00100000; PDE[0] REMOVED after jump
MMIO identity map: 0xB8000=0xB8000; volatile uint16_t*; PTE PCD=1 uncacheable
__bss_start exported by ld as absolute symbol
__bss_end exported by ld as absolute symbol
VMA=LMA here (identity); higher-half uses offset in script
